---
title: Spinner
---

p.-text Loading Spinner is a progress indicator to indicate that the client wait while the browser waits for the results.

h3 Examples
p.-text
  | To display a Loading Spinner, use the class <code>a-spinner__backdrop</code> and <code>a-spinner</code>.
  | A contextual class (e.g. <code>-inverse</code>) can also be applied to provide alternate styling.

h3 Backdrop

h4 Base
.example.-mb3
  .a-spinner__backdrop.-p6(style="position:relative;height:25rem;")
    svg(class=`a-spinner -textBrand`,viewBox=`0 0 66 66`)
      title Loading
      circle(class=`path`,cx=`33`,cy=`33`,r=`30`,fill=`none`,stroke-width=`6`)
  :code(lang="html")
    <div class="a-spinner__backdrop">
      <svg class="a-spinner -textBrand" viewBox="0 0 66 66">
        <title>Loading</title>
        <circle class="path" cx="33" cy="33" r="30" fill="none" stroke-width="6"></circle>
      </svg>
    </div>

