h3 Spinner Sizes
p.-text By default, Spinner render at 16x16px (<code>-sm</code>). Apply size classes to render Spinner larger or smaller:
  | <code>-xs</code>, <code>-sm</code>, <code>-md</code>, <code>-lg</code>, <code>-xl</code>, <code>-xxl</code>.
p.-text Two alternate small classes are available for specific app scenarios. Use <code>-sm2</code> for
  |  displaying 20px spinners within a 40px container (e.g. large button), and <code>-sm3</code> for displaying
  | 24px spinners within a 48px container.
.example.-mb3
  .-p3
    .a-grid.-align-items--end
      each size in ['xs', 'sm', 'md', 'lg', 'xl', 'xxl']
        div.-p2
          svg(class=`a-spinner -${size} -m3`,viewBox=`0 0 66 66`)
            title Loading
            circle(class=`path`,cx=`33`,cy=`33`,r=`30`,fill=`none`,stroke-width=`6`)
  :code(lang="html")
    <!-- -xs : 12x12px -->
    <svg class="a-spinner -xs" viewBox="0 0 66 66">
      <title>Loading</title>
      <circle class="path" cx="33" cy="33" r="30" fill="none" stroke-width="6"></circle>
    </svg>
